            <title>[SWF-745] Enhance FlowPhaseListener to have it maintain FacesMessages accross client side redirects</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SWF-745</link>
                <project id="10050" key="SWF">Spring Web Flow</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FacesMessages are stored inside the FacesContext which is tied to a request/thread. As a result, they are lost when using POST-REDIRECT-GET (alwaysRedirectOnPause). The FlowPhaseListener should be enhanced to temporarily store them away in flash scope.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
